President Vladimir Putin of Russia has signed a law on administrative liability for violation of the time frame and procedure for payment of goods (work, services) in procurement for State and municipal needs.
This law is intended to address very acute failure by employers to comply with their obligations in the conduct of public and municipal procurement.
A further two years ago, the situation where entrepreneurs were unable to receive payment under existing State and municipal contracts was widespread.
At the same time, the President of Russia instructed the Office of the Attorney General of the Russian Federation to take on special control.
Because the businessmen themselves were unable to deal with unfair employers who entered into unfunded contracts, they tried to avoid the obligations they had entered into and included illegal conditions in the contracts.
The problem was systemic in the whole country.
Since 2015, in order to protect the rights of entrepreneurs to receive payment on public orders, the Public Prosecutor ' s Office has submitted 9,700 submissions, 4,500 officials have been prosecuted, 533 administrative officers have been brought to the investigative bodies for the conduct of the procedural reviews, and 46 of them have initiated criminal proceedings.
As a result, over 66 billion roubles were owed to entrepreneurs.
However, these enormous amounts have not been accumulated as a result of the non-payment of multi-billion contracts.
Baseline debts have resulted in numerous, systematic delays in payment of services to entrepreneurs by far more modest amounts.
This is a typical case.
The manager of the small company won a competition for social transport services for several million roubles.
Man has invested all his working capitals, has fully fulfilled his obligations, but has not received the money in time.
The result is a growing financial casing of arrears in wages, taxes, loans that would result in bankruptcy if the employer did not seek assistance from the Public Prosecutor ' s Office.
The problem has now been addressed in a number of regions as much as possible.
However, as of the first half of the year 2017, the total amount of public and municipal debt identified by prosecutors of the entities of the Russian Federation was about 27.4 billion roubles.
In regions where debt rates continue to reach critical levels, the Public Prosecutor ' s Office operates in a manual anti-crisis management system.
The Attorney-General personally holds visiting meetings with representatives of the local authorities, at which all violations and measures to remedy them are dealt with in detail by prosecutors.
Such operational meetings have already taken place in Yaroslavl and Ekaterinburg this year.
The implementation of Federal Act No. 189-FZ on the amendment of the Code of Administrative Offences to establish administrative liability for the employer's officials for the violation of the length and manner of payment of goods, construction, services, and procurement for State and municipal needs, which was signed last week by the President of Russia, will be able to improve the payment of payment to public customers.
The draft law was drafted by the Ministry of Development of Russia on the initiative of the Office of the Attorney-General.
The new law will supplement the Code of Administrative Offences of the Russian Federation with an article which provides for a fine of between 30,000 and 50,000 roubles for violation by an official of the order and procedure for payment of goods, works and services in public and municipal procurement.
If an official has already been subjected to administrative punishment for a similar offence, he will be disqualified for a period of one to two years.
All prosecutors of the constituent entities of the Russian Federation have already been instructed to enforce these legislative innovations in practice.
