In Ukraine, Russian prisoners were proposed for illegal border crossing
The Supreme Council of Ukraine has registered a draft law under which a criminal penalty may be imposed on Russians for illegal crossing the Ukrainian border.
As the TV channel RT broadcasts, a document recorded in the Ukrainian Parliament's electronic database implies a three-year prison sentence for Russian citizens trying to enter the country illegally.
It is noted that for a repeated offence or act committed by a group of persons, the sentence of imprisonment may be extended to five years.
If the perpetrator was detained on the border with arms, the time spent in detention would increase to eight years.
It was previously reported that Ukrainian border guards had detained Ukrainians trying to enter Russia outside the designated points.
